        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 23 at 4:31PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 431 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles south of Bryson City, moving northwest at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bryson City, Smoky Mountains-Deep Creek, Cherokee, Fontana Lake,
Wesser, Stecoah, Burningtown, Savannah, Whittier, and Cowee.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
